span id=3D"dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it=3D"false"></span>
<p>Cooks and chefs often follow a recipe when cooking. A good cook measures=
 the needed ingredients with accuracy. Knowing how many cups in a pint is e=
ssential to following many recipes.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" width=3D=
"1200" height=3D"798" src=3D"https://livelytable.com/wp-content/uploads/coo=
king-coversions/How-Many-Cups-in-a-Pint.jpg" alt=3D"How Many Cups in a Pint=
?" data-skip-lazy=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-27957" data-pin-media=3D"https://l=
ivelytable.com/wp-content/uploads/cooking-coversions/How-Many-Cups-in-a-Pin=
t.jpg" data-pin-description=3D"How Many Cups in a Pint?" data-pin-title=3D"=
How Many Cups in a Pint?"></figure>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-a-cup" style=3D"text-transfo=
rm:capitalize"><strong>What Is a Cup?</strong></h2>



<p>A<a href=3D"https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/cup" data-wpel-li=
nk=3D"external" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"external noopener noreferrer" clas=
s=3D"wpel-icon-right"> cup<span class=3D"wpel-icon wpel-image wpel-icon-3">=
</span></a> is a unit of volume measurement in the United States. The cup i=
s used in both dry and liquid measurements for cooking and baking recipes. =
It is also used for measuring individual servings of food, such as cereal o=
r ice cream. One cup is equivalent to<a href=3D"https://livelytable.com/coo=
king-conversions/how-many-ounces-in-a-cup/" data-wpel-link=3D"internal"> 8 =
fluid ounces</a>, 16 tablespoons, =C2=BC quart, or about 237 milliliters. T=
he<a href=3D"https://www.nist.gov/pml/owm/approximate-conversions-us-custom=
ary-measures-metric" data-wpel-link=3D"external" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"e=
xternal noopener noreferrer" class=3D"wpel-icon-right"> abbreviation for cu=
p<span class=3D"wpel-icon wpel-image wpel-icon-3"></span></a> is <em>c</em>=
.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-a-pint" style=3D"text-transf=
orm:capitalize"><strong>What Is a Pint?</strong></h2>



<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true">A pint in the United States also mea=
sures volume. Pints are often used when measuring liquid ingredients for re=
cipes. A pint is equivalent to 16 fluid ounces, 32 tablespoons, =C2=BD quar=
t, or about 473 milliliters. This is different from a British imperial pint=
, which is 20 fluid ounces. The<a href=3D"https://www.nist.gov/pml/owm/appr=
oximate-conversions-us-customary-measures-metric" data-wpel-link=3D"externa=
l" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"external noopener noreferrer" class=3D"wpel-ico=
n-right"> abbreviation for pint<span class=3D"wpel-icon wpel-image wpel-ico=
n-3"></span></a> is <em>pt</em>.</p>
