p>



<p>Number of cups =3D Number of pints =C3=97 2</p>



<p>For example, if you want to know how many cups are in 4 pints, you multi=
ply 2 by 4.</p>



<p>Number of cups =3D Number of pints =C3=97 2</p>



<p>Number of cups =3D 4 =C3=97 2</p>



<p>Number of cups =3D 8</p>



<p>So, there are 8 cups in 4 pints.</p>



